[Unfortunately, there continues to be significant circulation of both the wild polioviruses (WPV) and the circulating vaccine-derived polioviruses (cVDPV) documented in the above weekly report. While there are no newly confirmed cases of WPV-associated disease, the WPV has been isolated from multiple locations in both Pakistan (all 4 provinces with positive environmental samples) as well as Afghanistan (Hilmand, Kandahar, and Nangarhar provinces). If one reads the article below, one sees there have been 2 newly confirmed cases reported in Pakistan, not as yet included in the weekly global summaries.

As for the cVDPVs, Nigeria has reported its 3rd case in the recently newly identified state of Kwara, but environmental samples were positive for cVDPVs in 4 other states (Borno, Kano, Tobe, and Katsina). In Niger, cVDPV2 were isolated from 5 healthy contacts in Zinder region, and in Indonesia, 1 cVDPV1 was isolated from a healthy contact with the sample taken in February 2019.

For a map showing the locations of cases of WPV and cVDPV, see http://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/.

