******
[2] Pakistan: 2 new cases (Sindh, FATA)
Date: Thu 21 Mar 2019
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
https://tribune.com.pk/story/1934333/1-karachi-reports-first-polio-case-year/


Two new polio cases emerged in Khyber tribal district and Karachi on Thursday [21 Mar 2019], bringing the total number of cases to 6 in the ongoing year [2019].

While a 12-month-old toddler from Landi Kotal contracted the virus, the victim from Karachi is a 3-year-old minor.

According to focal person on polio eradication Babar Atta, the cases are symptoms of an underlying problem: heavy virus circulation in sewage and the environment. "On PowerPoint, everything is a green, [but] on ground a big fat red," he tweeted.

A separate statement issued by the Sindh government gave details on the case from Karachi: "It is with great regret that we announce the 1st polio case of Sindh in 2019, as a 36-month-old female child has tested positive for the virus in UC 9 Lyari town," the communique read.

The statement quoted provincial DG Health Masood Solangi claiming that the child had received oral polio vaccine multiple times; however, she had a history of illness, suffered from malnourishment, and was low on immunity, and hence developed weakness in her limbs.

"However, the child will not suffer from paralysis, as she was vaccinated with OPV on multiple occasions and has fully recovered," he was quoted as saying.

Coordinator [of the] emergency operation center of the Polio Eradication Initiative Umer Farooq Bullo said, "The Sindh government will respond strongly, and a campaign is planned in the city from [25 Mar 2019."

He urged parents to take responsibility and comply with recommendations given by health experts and cooperate with polio teams.

A total 12 poliovirus cases were reported from the country in 2018.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Positive environmental samples in KP Tribal Areas and Sindh (Karachi) can be explained by the identification of 2 new cases. The addition of these cases to the global total will increase the global total of reported cases associated with WPV infection to 8, and that of Pakistan to 6. A table showing the distribution of reported cases by province and year can be found at http://www.endpolio.com.pk/polioin-pakistan/polio-cases-in-provinces.

Given the described recovery of the case in Sindh, it is unclear if this case will be reported as a confirmed case. We await further information on this case. - Mod.MPP]
